<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="160" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d160">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/2513</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-21">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 21, 1918</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I approve of the course
                            proposed in this letter. I take it for granted that everything necessary
                            would be done to protect the Chinese Government against such
                            unconscionable arrangements as were contemplated by the former
                            consortium, because I am afraid it is not less but rather more likely
                            that the Chinese Government would permit unfair advantage to be taken of
                            it at the present time of stress than formerly.</p>
                        <p>Cordially and sincerely yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>